  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    com.squareup.okhttp.OkHttpClient.createURLStreamHandler(String)
    moved to OkUrlFactory.createURLStreamHandler.
    com.squareup.okhttp.OkHttpClient.getFollowProtocolRedirects()
    moved to OkHttpClient.getFollowSslRedirects().
    com.squareup.okhttp.OkHttpClient.getOkResponseCache()
    replaced by OkHttpClient.getCache() which doesn't support custom cache implementations.
    com.squareup.okhttp.OkHttpClient.getResponseCache()
    replaced by OkHttpClient.getCache() which doesn't support custom cache implementations.
    com.squareup.okhttp.OkHttpClient.getRoutesDatabase()
    removed from the public API in OkHttp 2.0.
    com.squareup.okhttp.OkHttpClient.getTransports()
    OkHttp 1.5 enforces an enumeration of protocols that can be selected. Please switch to OkHttpClient.getProtocols().
    com.squareup.okhttp.Route.isModernTls()
    replaced with Route.getTlsVersion() in OkHttp 2.0.
    com.squareup.okhttp.OkHttpClient.open(URL)
    moved to OkUrlFactory.open.
    com.squareup.okhttp.OkHttpClient.setFollowProtocolRedirects(boolean)
    moved to OkHttpClient.setFollowSslRedirects(boolean).
    com.squareup.okhttp.OkHttpClient.setOkResponseCache(OkResponseCache)
    replaced by OkHttpClient.setCache(com.squareup.okhttp.Cache) which doesn't support custom cache implementations.
    com.squareup.okhttp.OkHttpClient.setResponseCache(ResponseCache)
    replaced by OkHttpClient.setCache(com.squareup.okhttp.Cache) which doesn't support custom cache implementations.
    com.squareup.okhttp.OkHttpClient.setTransports(List)
    OkHttp 1.5 enforces an enumeration of protocols that can be selected. Please switch to OkHttpClient.setProtocols(java.util.List).
